Devices appear in Photos and Albums view. The device can be ejected from within Photos.

flowRoot.flowPara: The ongoing import process is always communicated, but most actions can be performed (editing, favoriting, renaming, sharing).
Photos that have already been imported do not show up in the view. All photos are selected to be imported by default.

As smartphones are slowly (well rather fast) killing compact cameras, this is going to lose to direct cloud upload directly from the device eventually. But for the meantime, this would be the default mean to populate the photo library.
Camera connects through a USB cable or via wifi to the home network.

text.tspan: Number of unimported photos (checked for duplicates)

flowRoot.flowPara: Import is non-blocking, with potential data loss if the user prematurely yanks the card mechanically. Technical detail: would be nice to store hashes of yet to be imported photos similar to thos for checking for duplicates to be able to undo the yank action. Trigger a warning notification when the card is yanked, allow to reinsert, figure the remaining files to reimport and resume without asking.
When the device is attached while the app is open, regardless of the view presented, an in-app notification is shown.
When the Photos app isn't focused and a device containing photos is connected, a system notification is shown.
A new album is created for the photos by default, with the date of the last photo taken. The name is selected by default so it can be renamed immediately.
When adding photos to an existing album, the last four used (viewed or created) albums are shown. Type to search shows 4 top results for the query.
